This paper discusses the problem of replicating human common-sense reasoning in artificial intelligence, which is a central topic in the field of AI (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a computational formalism centered around a probabilistic Turing machine, which is related to machine learning and probabilistic modeling (cs.LG). The use of a Turing machine also suggests a connection to theoretical computer science and complexity theory (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the foundations of computation and statistics, which could be relevant to logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL).
